The occupation itsels was called Carnuficina‚ Cist. 11. i. 1; and those who practised it were said carmeficinam facere, Capt. I. ii. 29, equivalent to which is facere quaestum carcerarium, v. 26. The employment was by no means honourable nor popular, and hence no term of vituperation is more common than carnufex.
